speechtext:
Mr. Speaker, I think you would find there is unanimous consent in the House to adjourn this debate to accommodate a debate on the Special Economic Measures Act order. If that consent exists, I would then move:
Thai, notwithstanding any Standing Order, upon the calling of the Special Economic Measures Act order, the Speaker shall put all questions necessary to dispose of the order at no later than 5.30 p.m. on Tuesday, December 8, 1992 and that if a recorded division is requested, it shall be deferred until 3 p.m. on Wednesday, December 9, 1992;
That, the time provided for Private Members' Business be from 5.30 to 6.30 p.m. on Tuesday, December 8, 1992, after which the Speaker shall adjourn the House until Wednesday, December 9, 1992.
